criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. the one who is or is between 65 to 85 years old, male or female;

          2. the one with nutritional risk according to MNA-Short Form evaluation (score less
             than12);

          3. the one who has low skeletal muscle mass (with bioelectrical impedance analysis report
             indicating that the skeletal muscle mass is less than 90% of the normal level) and/or
             the one who has at least 1 type of the micronutrient deficiency symptom (part A < 40
             or part A < 85 in the hidden hungry evaluation questionnaire)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. long-term bedridden or the one has difficult in taking food orally;

          2. Liver failure in recent one year;

          3. Renal insufficiency (serum creatinine is more than 2 times of normal value)

          4. the one who is allergic to or not applicable to the component in oral dietary
             supplement;

          5. the one with parkinsonism, epilepsy and other nervous system disorders;

          6. malignant tumor patients with chemotherapy and chemotherapy;

          7. irritable bowel disease and other chronic wasting diseases.

          8. Taking multi-vitamin&mineral supplements or protein or other oral nutritional
             supplements
